The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is muscle fiber, sarcomere, myofibril, sarcoplasmic reticulum, and T-tubule. A muscle fiber is a single cell in the skeletal muscle tissue. The muscle fiber contains myofibrils, which are the contractile units of the muscle. The myofibrils are composed of sarcomeres, which are the contractile units of the muscle. The sarcomeres are composed of myofilaments, which are the contractile proteins of the muscle. The myofilaments are composed of actin and myosin.
